<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 [&_h1]:text-3xl [&_h1]:font-bold [&_h1]:mb-2 [&_h2]:text-xl [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h2]:mt-8 [&_h2]:mb-3 [&_p]:mb-4 [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_ul]:mb-4 [&_ul]:space-y-1 [&_a]:text-primary [&_a]:underline">
  <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
  <p class="text-base-content/60">Last updated: March 8, 2026</p>

  <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
  <p>
    By accessing or using MetricFlow ("the Service"), operated at
    <a href="https://metric-flow.app">metric-flow.app</a>, you agree to be bound by these Terms of
    Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the Service.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
  <p>
    MetricFlow is a marketing and financial data platform that allows you to connect third-party
    accounts (such as Google Ads, Google Analytics, Facebook Ads, and others) via OAuth, sync
    metrics, view unified dashboards, perform correlation analysis, and access AI-powered insights.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Account Registration</h2>
  <p>To use the Service, you must:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Create an account with a valid email address</li>
    <li>Provide accurate and complete information</li>
    <li>Maintain the security of your password and account</li>
    <li>Notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You are responsible for all activity that occurs under your account.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Platform Integrations</h2>
  <p>
    The Service allows you to connect third-party platforms through OAuth authorization. By connecting
    a platform, you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Authorize MetricFlow to access your data on that platform as described during the OAuth consent flow</li>
    <li>Confirm that you have the authority to grant such access</li>
    <li>Understand that MetricFlow will sync and store metrics from your connected accounts</li>
    <li>May disconnect any integration at any time through the Integrations settings</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    MetricFlow is not responsible for changes to third-party platform APIs, service interruptions, or
    data accuracy from connected platforms.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any applicable laws</li>
    <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service, other accounts, or connected systems</li>
    <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service or its infrastructure</li>
    <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any part of the Service</li>
    <li>Use the Service to collect data about other users without their consent</li>
    <li>Resell or redistribute access to the Service without authorization</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Agency and Team Access</h2>
  <p>
    The Service supports multi-user accounts and agency white-label features. If you are an agency
    granting access to clients, or a client accepting an invitation:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Agency administrators are responsible for managing team member access levels</li>
    <li>Access permissions are determined by the account owner or agency administrator</li>
    <li>Client data remains the property of the client; agencies access it under the terms of their own agreements with clients</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. AI-Powered Features</h2>
  <p>
    The Service includes AI-powered features (insights, chat, anomaly detection). These features:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Are provided for informational purposes and should not be treated as professional financial or marketing advice</li>
    <li>May use third-party AI models to process your metric data</li>
    <li>May produce inaccurate or incomplete results; you are responsible for verifying AI-generated content before acting on it</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>
    The Service and its original content, features, and functionality are owned by MetricFlow and are
    protected by applicable intellectual property laws. Your data remains yours &mdash; we claim no
